-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Refiner Mol Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-02T15:41:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
fell 0.3 percent to 18,578.36 as of the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, added as
much as 1.3 percent as the country’s manufacturing confidence
index rose to the highest in a year in March. The stock last
traded 0.2 percent lower at 3,820 forint.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, jumped as
much as 1 percent to 18,590 forint as oil climbed for a second
day in New York. The company’s shares closed 0.4 percent lower.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
